COMPANY: Seven.One Entertainment Group
ROLE TITLE: Lead Software Engineer / Technical Architect
PERIOD: 2020–Present

DOMAIN AREAS:
AdTech • Cloud Architecture • Software Modernization

BACKGROUND CONTEXT:
When I joined, the TV advertising platform was in a critical state — a monolithic legacy stack powering millions of ad impressions per day, burdened by years of rapid feature growth without architectural discipline. Releases were risky, engineers were leaving due to system fragility, and business stakeholders were losing confidence. The leadership needed someone to stabilize delivery, reduce outages, and create an architectural path toward scalability and innovation. The business could not be stopped and features could not be stopped from being developed as a multitude of stakeholders were involved.

SITUATION:
Legacy monolith causing slow delivery and fragile deployments across the AdTech platform. Heavy technical debt with a monolith serving diverse needs with different non-functional requirements; the codebase was a spaghetti of JS and TS files with callback hell and many dependent modules that were very hard to debug and understand, especially for new joiners. This led to bugs, hard-to-understand code, and difficulty speeding up time-to-market for features.

TASK:
Refactor and stabilize the system while maintaining continuous delivery for millions of ad impressions. Take ownership of technical debt, assess its causes and consequences, and strategically come up with a plan and execution strategy to reduce it while fulfilling all other constraints and ensuring the business still works and delivers on time.

ACTIONS:
• Led a multi-year modernization effort, decomposing monolith into event-driven microservices
• Led a multi-dimensional multi-year refactoring and modernization of large-scale legacy system, creating choreographed autonomous event-driven microservices that led to resilient state-of-the-art system that persisted tough conditions, errors and bugs
• Introduced Domain-Driven Design (DDD) and ubiquitous language to align tech and business teams and model the business consistently
• Implemented AWS-based CI/CD pipelines, observability, and fault-tolerant architecture

RESULTS:
• Reduced incidents by 75%
• Improved release cycle time from weeks to days
• Onboarded new engineers 50% faster (from 6 months to 3 months)
• Improved delivery predictability by 25%
• No downtime reported in 3 straight years

IMPACT SUMMARY:
Transformed a fragile legacy advertising platform into a scalable, reliable, cloud-native architecture. Technical health of the whole ecosystem massively improved, freeing up resources to focus on innovation and revenue generation and other key differentiating business value activities. This transformed a fragile legacy advertising system into a modern, auditable, cloud-native architecture that now supports long-term scalability, resilience, cross-team velocity, and business transparency.

CONDENSED VERSION:
Led modernization of AdTech platform from monolith to event-driven microservices using DDD and AWS. Reduced incidents by 75%, improved release cadence from weeks to days. Increased reliability and team efficiency through domain-driven design and automation.

