BACKGROUND CONTEXT:
The EU's GDPR regulation mandated strict consent management for digital advertising, and the IAB Europe's Transparency and Consent Framework (TCF) became the industry standard. Our HbbTV advertising platform was generating 30M euros in annual revenue but lacked TCF-compliant consent management. Without compliance, we risked massive fines and complete advertising shutdown. The project had extreme time pressure, legal scrutiny, and zero margin for error—any failure would immediately halt all ad delivery and revenue.

SITUATION:
Addressable TV platform generating 30M euros annual revenue faced existential compliance risk. Existing consent management implementation was not TCF 2.0 compliant, putting the entire advertising business at regulatory and legal risk. Multiple successful GDPR audits were required, and failure would result in immediate revenue loss and potential multi-million euro fines.

TASK:
Lead the rapid development and deployment of a TCF 2.0 compliant Consent Management Platform (CMP) for HbbTV environment, ensure it passes multiple rigorous GDPR audits, and preserve 30M euros in annual advertising revenue while meeting aggressive legal deadlines.

ACTIONS:
• Led technical assessment of TCF 2.0 requirements and HbbTV platform constraints, translating complex legal requirements into technical specifications
• Architected CMP solution integrating with existing ad delivery infrastructure while ensuring zero disruption to live advertising operations
• Implemented TCF 2.0 API specifications, consent string encoding/decoding, and vendor list management according to IAB Europe standards
• Designed user consent interfaces optimized for TV remote control navigation and HbbTV JavaScript runtime limitations
• Coordinated closely with legal counsel, privacy officers, product managers, and QA teams to ensure comprehensive compliance coverage
• Established rigorous testing protocols covering consent flows, data handling, vendor integration, and audit trail requirements
• Successfully led platform through multiple GDPR compliance audits with external auditors
• Implemented monitoring and alerting for consent-related errors to maintain ongoing compliance


