/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:44","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:142"],"citation":"Greenfield evidence is curated in [02_samdock_daypaio.md:27], [02_samdock_daypaio.md:44], and [02_samdock_daypaio.md:142] but is not reflected in the current top-level representation anchored by [01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28]."},{"signal":"Consulting-style workshop and stakeholder-translation evidence","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"Global/remote AI architect roles often reward architects who can run workshops, translate requirements, and align client or enterprise stakeholders.","current_state":"Stakeholder collaboration exists across Seven.One, Samdock, and Clary Icon, but it is not intentionally surfaced as architect-style workshop/translation proof.","safe_interpretation":"The record supports stakeholder translation, event-storming facilitation, and direct client collaboration; it does not automatically support a default customer-facing solution architect identity.","recommended_action":"Surface stakeholder workshops, event storming, and direct client communication as secondary architect signals tied to delivery outcomes.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:250","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:44","data/master-cv/roles/06_clary_icon.md:103"],"citation":"Supported and curated in [01_seven_one_entertainment.md:250], [02_samdock_daypaio.md:44], and [06_clary_icon.md:103], but underrepresented in the current representation."},{"signal":"Explicit agent-workflow ownership beyond tool-calling and workflow plugins","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"The category rewards agent/orchestration proof, but overstating from adjacent evidence would create credibility risk.","current_state":"Curated evidence shows workflow plugins, MCP tools, guardrail injection, structured outputs, and enterprise AI workflow delivery, but does not explicitly prove shipped autonomous agent workflows or broad agentic ownership.","safe_interpretation":"Safe wording is MCP tools, workflow plugins, tool-calling architecture, and enterprise AI workflows; broad 'agentic AI leader' wording is too strong.","recommended_action":"Keep agent-language subordinate until explicit shipped agent workflows, routing logic, or agent-operability outcomes are curated with provenance.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9"],"citation":"Current evidence supports integration and workflow architecture in [01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332] and [projects/commander4.md:9], but not a stronger autonomous-agent claim."},{"signal":"AI-specific outcome metrics concentrated in top bullets","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"Architect profiles become more competitive when AI architecture claims are paired with visible quality, latency, cost, and scale outcomes.","current_state":"The curated record contains AI metrics and outcome fragments, but the top representation does not consolidate them into flagship bullets.","safe_interpretation":"Safe metrics include 2,000 users, 42 plugins, 14 tests, ~2ms L1 cache, ~200ms L2 cache, and ~40% redundant API-spend reduction in testing.","recommended_action":"Promote AI-specific scale/quality/cost metrics into top role/project bullets rather than leaving them dispersed across project lines and lower-level evidence.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:354","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:8"],"citation":"Metrics exist in [01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282], [01_seven_one_entertainment.md:354], [projects/commander4.md:8], and [projects/lantern.md:8], but are not concentrated in current top-level representation."},{"signal":"AI compliance ownership and region-specific regulation authority","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"This category values governance, but unsafe compliance inflation would weaken credibility for global remote architect roles.","current_state":"Curated evidence proves GDPR/TCF delivery in AdTech and guardrail/access-control design in AI systems, but not ownership of AI compliance programs, EU AI Act implementation, or broad regulatory authority for AI.","safe_interpretation":"Safe wording is guardrails, access control, structured outputs, and prior compliance delivery experience in non-AI systems.","recommended_action":"Avoid claiming AI compliance ownership; keep governance language tied to technical controls already evidenced.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:106","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332"],"citation":"[01_seven_one_entertainment.md:106] supports GDPR/TCF delivery and [01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332] supports AI guardrails, but neither safely supports AI compliance-owner positioning."},{"signal":"Provider-branded or multi-cloud AI architect positioning","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"The blueprint explicitly warns against default cloud-authority branding when provider evidence is supporting rather than category-defining.","current_state":"AWS delivery is strong in modernization work, and Lantern shows multi-provider routing across OpenAI, Anthropic, and Azure endpoints, but this is not the same as broad provider-authority or multi-cloud architect branding.","safe_interpretation":"Safe wording is AWS-backed modernization plus multi-provider LLM gateway design; unsafe wording is defaulting to AWS/Azure or multi-cloud AI architect authority.","recommended_action":"Keep provider names as supporting bullets rather than headline anchors unless future curation adds broader platform scope.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:7"],"citation":"Supported provider-adjacent evidence exists in [01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28] and [projects/lantern.md:7], but broader authority claims would still overreach."}],"safe_claims_now":{"headline_safe":["AI Architect | Enterprise AI Platforms, RAG, Evaluation & Guardrails","AI Solution Architect | Enterprise Integration, MCP Tools, Workflow Platforms","Software Architect | AI Platforms, Modernization, Distributed Systems"],"profile_safe":["Senior architect-first IC who designs enterprise AI platforms and carries target architectures into production systems.","Hands-on architect with evidence in hybrid retrieval, evaluation harnesses, semantic caching, structured outputs, model routing, and governance controls.","Enterprise modernization architect whose distributed-systems foundation strengthens GenAI delivery credibility."],"experience_safe":["Platform lead for an enterprise AI workflow platform serving 2,000 users with 42 plugins.","Designed structured-output and tool-calling architecture with 5 MCP tools, per-silo guardrails, and access control.","Built hybrid retrieval, LLM-as-judge reranking, semantic caching, and retrieval evaluation for enterprise AI search quality.","Transformed a legacy AdTech platform into event-driven AWS microservices with 75% incident reduction and 3 years zero downtime.","Architected and launched a 0→1 event-sourced CRM platform that went live with 25 production tenants."],"leadership_safe":["Established architectural north-star direction and educated stakeholders on technical-debt ROI.","Mentored 10+ engineers on architecture and cloud patterns, with 3 promoted to lead roles.","Facilitated stakeholder workshops and domain discovery through event storming and business-metric translation."],"unsafe_or_too_weak":["Head of AI, Director of AI, VP AI, or other executive AI ownership titles.","Agentic AI leader phrasing that implies shipped autonomous-agent programs rather than evidenced workflow/tool integrations.","AI compliance owner, EU AI Act authority, or responsible-AI program ownership.","Multi-cloud AI architect authority as a default brand.","Formal people-manager or org-builder identity as the primary category frame.","Research-heavy, fine-tuning, RLHF, or advanced-experimentation positioning."],"citations":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:27","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:44","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:7","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8"]},"representation_diagnosis":{"well_represented_now":["The current representation already shows strong legacy modernization and distributed-systems architecture proof from Seven.One.","Commander-4 and Lantern projects visibly surface RAG, gateway, caching, and evaluation depth.","The skill stack already contains many of the right AI-platform keywords, including RAG Pipeline, Retrieval Evaluation, MCP Tool Design, LLM Gateway Design, and Model Routing."],"underrepresented_now":["AI architect branding is weaker than the underlying evidence and is not the default top-line identity.","Guardrails, structured outputs, MCP integrations, and access control are not central in the current summary despite being high-value category signals.","Greenfield architecture and workshop-style stakeholder facilitation are present in curated evidence but not part of the current top narrative.","Player-coach leadership is supported, but the present 'Engineering Leader' phrasing risks reading manager-first instead of architect-first."],"overstated_risk_now":["The headline 'Engineering Leader / Software Architect' can be read as broader management scope than the evidence needs for this category.","The current summary overweights AdTech modernization and underweights curr